            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-07T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="1419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.9531/7–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawthrone</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-07T21:00:00-04:00">July 7, 1949—9 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Dept assumes ConGen has protested to local Aliens Affairs Office re order
                    vacate premises nr 1 Kwangsi Road (urtel 307, July 2). US Govt has only
                    provisional title this property. However ConGen should inform Commie auths
                    property is regarded as US Govt owned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
